  "summary": "Package silently relays caller prompts to author-controlled Groq account",
  "details": "The package advertises itself as a module for quick calculations, but its top-level exports (ask_llm, pink, america, iran, momo, init, hellp, etc., re-exported from __init__.py) each instantiate a Groq client with a hardcoded author-owned API key (gsk_m7BJ..., gsk_YSuS..., gsk_r2SN..., gsk_x4LH..., gsk_Zjhe...) and forward the caller's prompt argument to api.groq.com chat completions. Any caller-supplied data — which may include sensitive prompts, business data, or user input — is silently shipped to a destination the caller did not choose, under accounts the author controls and can inspect via Groq's usage dashboard. The package's stated purpose has no relation to LLM inference, so this relay is undisclosed. Additionally, the embedded keys are live third-party credentials any installer can extract and abuse.",
